<|startoftext|>Dish: cornstarch granule bars
Directions: preheat oven to 350
combine the cornstarch and water and let it sit until it starts to set up
preheat the oven to 375 and melt the butter , stirring often , over a medium heat
add the powdered sugar and stir , cook for 5 minutes , or until the sugar crystals are golden , stirring a few times
mix well and keep warm
sift together the cornstarch and flour
add to the butter mixture alternately with the cold butter mixture in two mixtures
stirring once , until combined well , but this is a thin consistency , and add enough additional flour to give a thin batter
pour into a greased 9 inch square pan and bake for 20-25 minutes , or until golden brown and firm to the touch
allow the pan to cool on a rack for 10 minutes and then remove the pan from the oven and cool completely on the rack while you make your sauce'<|endoftext|>
